    "body": "<!-- Before reporting: search existing issues and check the FAQ. -->\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`:\r\n    ```\r\n    NVIM v0.4.2\r\n    Build type: Release\r\n    LuaJIT 2.1.0-beta3\r\n    Compilation: \r\n    Compiled by nixbld1\r\n\r\n    Features: +acl +iconv +tui\r\n    See \":help feature-compile\"\r\n\r\n      system vimrc file: \"$VIM/sysinit.vim\"\r\n      fall-back for $VIM: \"\r\n    /nix/store/2hg5nc9l57691wgplplqnhjxz5rqf7sy-neovim-unwrapped-0.4.2/share/nvim\r\n    \"\r\n\r\n    Run :checkhealth for more info\r\n    ```\r\n- `vim -u DEFAULTS` (version: ) behaves differently? No\r\n- Operating system/version: `Darwin NiunioBook.local 18.7.0 Darwin Kernel Version 18.7.0: Sat Oct 12 00:02:19 PDT 2019; root:xnu-4903.278.12~1/RELEASE_X86_64 x86_64 i386 MacBookPro15,1 Darwin`\r\n- Terminal name/version: `kitty 0.14.6 created by Kovid Goyal`\r\n- `$TERM`: `xterm-256color`\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim -u NORC\r\n:tab term\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nReplaces current buffer with new terminal buffer.\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nOpens new tab with terminal buffer.\r\n\r\n### Current workaround\r\n\r\n```\r\n:tabnew +term\r\n```\r\n\r\nOr\r\n\r\n```\r\n:tab split +term\r\n```",
    "closed_at": "2023-08-28T12:22:21Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I think this may break the compatibility.\r\n\r\nMaybe the best way is to add `:sterm` command to behave like `:split +term`, which is also how `:sbuffer`, `:sview`, `:snext`, etc work. \r\n\r\nI believe \r\n\r\n```\r\ncabbrev sterm split<bar>term\r\n```\r\nwould do the trick.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
